the request, if the request is denied.
SB57 INTRODUCED
29 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
30 Section 1. (a) For the purposes of this section, the
31 following terms have the following meanings:
32 (1) CANDY. Foods that list sugar, cane sugar, corn
33 syrup, or high fructose corn syrup as the first ingredient.
34 The term includes foods that include any food altered from its
35 natural state through processes including, but not limited to,
36 heating, mixing, milling, canning, freezing, or adding
37 ingredients. The term does not include any granulated sugar,
38 raw sugar, or other single-ingredient sugars used for cooking
39 and baking.
40 (2) DEPARTMENT. The Alabama Department of Human
41 Resources.
42 (3) SNAP BENEFIT. A financial benefit, coupon, or
43 privilege available under the federal Supplemental Nutrition
44 Assistance Program, 7 U.S.C. Chapter 51.
45 (4) SODA. Beverages that list carbonated water and
46 sugar, cane sugar, corn syrup, or high fructose corn syrup as
47 the first two ingredients. The term does not include any
48 beverages that list aspartame or other low or non-caloric
49 sweeteners as one of the first two ingredients.
50 (5) USDA FOOD AND NUTRITION SERVICE. The United States
51 Department of Agriculture Food and Nutrition Service.
52 (b) The commissioner of the department shall request a
53 waiver from the USDA Food and Nutrition Service to authorize
54 the department to exclude candy and soda from the definition
55 of "eligible foods" under 7 C.F.R. § 271.2.
56 (c) If the waiver described in subsection (b) is
Page 2

(c) If the waiver described in subsection (b) is
SB57 INTRODUCED
57 approved by the USDA Food and Nutrition Service, the
58 department shall prohibit the use of SNAP benefits for the
59 purchase of candy and soda.
60 (d) If the waiver described in subsection (b) is
61 denied, the commissioner shall resubmit the request for a
62 waiver to the USDA Food and Nutrition Service annually until
63 approval is granted.
64 Section 2. This act shall become effective on October
65 1, 2026.
